File: South Africa needed penalties to see off Ghana in the Under 23 Afcon's Bronze medal play-off. JOHANNESBURG - South Africa will have a football representative at the Tokyo 2020 Olympics. The men's under 23 side booked their ticket to next year's showpiece. But David Notoane's charges had to do it the hard way. READ: SA U23 to have second shot at Olympic dream South Africa needed penalties to see off Ghana in the Under 23 Afcon's bronze medal play-off. Earlier, the West Africans had come from behind twice to force a 2-all draw. South Africa beat 6-5 on penalties.